subSubSection.paragraph:
Aedeagus (
paratype
)

(
Fig. 16
). Basal piece slightly longer than wide, parallel-sided, dorsally open, basally bifid; remaining parts elongate, slightly constricted laterally at base of parameres, apically lobed; median lobe short and stout, shorter than parameres, apically rounded, narrowly bifid; parameres elongate, apically less sclerotized, with a triangular lateral tooth near base.
